<name>Vanessa Villanueva< /name><date>1559828346780<//date><Rating>5</Rating><text>I cannot overstate how wonderful this store is. Over the last few months I have had both a cat and a dog come into my life, and this store has been instrumental in helping me set up for their stay. Every single employee there is incredibly knowledgeable about pet care, and obviously genuinely love animals.

Their self serve wash station is also amazing! Very comprehensive, not just the water, but also the blow dryer, shampoo, towels, and little treats. Reasonable price too.

So lovely to have found them!< /text><Pics>None< /Pics><Resp>None</Resp><GmapID>0x80c2c04bca7d25a5:0xca991c3d5b1bb48< /GmapID></record></dataset><record>

0x80c2c04bca7d25a5:0xca991c3d5b1bb48< /gmap_id>
< Rate>
5</Rate>
<pics>None< /pics>< Review>
I have worked in the veterinary field, and I really appreciate the  care and enthusiasm the staff here puts into their work. They are well educated about the products, and they are always willing to take the time to help you find what you need. There is a good variety of product lines, but everything seems to be higher quality. Higher quality means their prices are a bit more than your superstore buys, but it is worth it to me, because I cannot find food suitable for my dogs' diet restrictions at mega- stores. Even with the grooming area in the back, the store is always clean. I have been to the Pasadena location, as well, and would say the same positive things.

The only downside for this Glendale location is parking. You have to get lucky with street parking. It is not a problem for me to have to walk a bit and carry my items, but I can see how it would be difficult for someone with mobility issues. The staff always offers to help out customers to their vehicles, which helps lessen that inconvenience.</Review>

Vanessa Vee< /Name>
<Date>1556911863463</Date><Rating>5</Rating>< Text>
I've never been to a more excellent pet supply store. I've visited a couple times already, and every employee I've talked to 1) obviously, genuinely loves animals and 2) is extremely knowledgeable and straightforward about the products on shelf and about pet care - grooming, nutrition, etc. Apparently the company has a division that researches and verifies information companies claim about their products, as well as educates it's employees.

The store itself is bright, clean, organized - and I can't stress enough how excellent the employees are. Absolutely trust them when it comes to the purchases for my animals.< /Text>

<pics>None< /pics><Name>Megan Romero<//Name>< text>
We rescued our 13 month old Siberian Husky about 10 months ago. We have done nothing but the best for her, including spending $$$$ at Pet Express Glendale on the very best food, treats and weekly baths.. up until yesterday our experiences have been absolutely great! Everyone was so helpful and made each visit a treat. Well our wild little pup somehow got underneath our home which unbeknownst to us is infested with fleas üòû and our poor all white baby was covered in fleas. We immediately got her out, sprayed the yard to kill all fleas (pet friendly and expensive stuff!!) and then raced her to Pet Express for a bath and some extra flea prevention. When we got there my husband went in and explain the situation, we had brought Dawn soap as we heard it was best and we just wanted to help our pup stop suffering. There was a gentleman there who told us we were right, dawn works best and helped set up my husband in the bathing area.. from there all the employees slowly came over one by one to look at our girl. I didn‚Äôt think much of it as they recommended topical flea solutions and other remedies to help avoid this in the future, Monah is on oral flea medication and until yesterday has never had even one flea on her. I went about my business, spent $30 on two tokens to wash her cause we felt like one bath wasn‚Äôt enough. Then the slap in the face cane, as I was walking around the store, I heard one gal talking about how horrible we were to allow this to happen and how our poor pup wasn‚Äôt been cared for and the rest of the employees chimed in. She made me feel so bad, my heart sank. The older gentleman realized I was in earshot and hushed everyone up rather quickly but needless to say the damage was done. We finished up with Monah and went to another pet store to buy the topical flea medicine they had suggested because at the end of the day I do want what is best for my girl but I refuse to help support that store anymore. I‚Äôd rather drive the extra few miles to the other Pet Express in Pasadena, better parking and less judgmental folks.< /text>

I have to share, today , my amazingly sweet and well behaved Staffordshire terrier that is loved by everyone was smelling a basket of treats and they accidentally fell down because quite obviously their structure wasn't right. One of the female employees all of a sudden got outraged,  stopped helping us, let everyone know how upset she was at my dog accidentally knocking down the basket and what a trouble it was for her to clean it up and mentioned she doesnt want to do this on her shift. The two females who's names I will not mention here continued to complain about the basket falling down accidentally, did  not want to ring me up and worst of all my Poor dog was SHAKING in FEAR because of how enraged that female was ! Glendale Petfood Express on Central.

< text>
Cute store.  The pet self wash station is very well set up, cheap, and convenient.  I do wish they offered an actual dryer to blow out dogs with a double coat though.  The warm air blower they offered BARELY dryed my short haired pit bull and didn't dry my long haired, double coated corgi literally at all.  I would come back simply because it's one of the only pet self washes around, but not necessarily because the facilities are super amazing.  Decent if you've got a short haired dog, but if you don't, just go to a groomer.<//text>

< review>
Basically had the worst anxiety at a medical club I've ever had. I'm a returning patient and having been coming to Telegraph Health Center for 3 years and I came in today (Nov 1st) and forgot I needed to update my medical recommendation and had to look for it in my email. As I was searching the woman at the front desk with glasses kept rushing me, saying "if I didn't have my rec I couldn't be in there". I suffer from an anxiety disorder and the woman at the front desk kept rushing me in a very aggressive manner making my anxiety flare.

I know I came in close to closing, but that doesn't mean I should be made to feel unwelcome and rushed. For a place dedicated to helping medicinal patients, this was definitely not conducive to healing whatsoever. A little bit of kindness and compassion go a long way.</review>

< review>
Nice little shop with cheap pricing for the area. The food itself was plentiful, though the quality was just okay. Not truly authentic Mexican food, but not so Americanized either: rather somewhat of an inbetween. Perhaps a good place for those not too familiar with Mexican cuisine, or simply are looking for a cheap and quick bite to eat. However the service was excellent!</review>

<user_name>Ileana Meliss</user_name><user>103401905446753766483< /user>< review>
I love this perfect hole-in-the-wall! In fact, most foods I love, come from these type of places.
It has intimate seating so be prepared to sit close with others. I see it as sitting with family. Even if we dont know eachother, Juanita Cafe has a way of making you feel welcomed as if you were one of their own. Lots of good memories and food come from this cute tiny kitchen. They've been here for years!
My Mum and her Mum have been going here for a long time, and then intruduced me to this place as a kid, and I've been going here ever since. When I can go, its definitely worth the drive!

The food is authentic! I go for their tequitos with EXTRA cheese, and their Guacamole and other sauces. Especially their handmade red sauce which is really spicy! They even have a yummy green chili sauce that may look simple however it sure packs a lot of flavor! I love this place! üíñ</review>

<response>None</response>< review>
This place is great. I'm new to City Heights from a small town in New Hampshire, and this place feels like home. All types of people shop here, but it's primarily a Mexican food store. It has lots of staple supplies, veggies, and the great darned chorizo I've ever had. The checkout staff is so nice, and the giant security guard at the front has a heart of gold. Even though everyone here is bilingual, I've even learned a little Spanish so I can impress these people. They learned English, so I should learn Spanish! The Mexican pastries and snacks are a little weird, but I love trying new things. This is a great neighborhood store, and I'm lucky to live right next door :)< /review>

Nice little grocery store. The selection is a bit limited as it's small, but it has fresh tortillas, a deli and a meat counter. The cashiers are usually very friendly. < Review>
Not sure how this Taqueria ranked so high on Yelp. The food is medicore at best. The cashier and cook did not understand the difference between grilled and griddled. Both salsa rojo and verde had a watery texture. The chicken was over salty and the flour tortilla was chewy because it was not warmed properly. I could go on but i will end with the fact, i will not be returning. I wasted $23.00. I would rather spend time and gas to eat in the Mission District. 3 stars is overrated.<//Review>

< review>
Their refills cost a buck! Was going to take away a star for predatory soda pricing unless the food was amazing.

The bulgogi burger combo was amazing!

Make sure to enhance your fries with the seasoning salt and tangy barbeque-but-not-quite sauce next to the ketchup.

The burger itself has no ground beef Patty, only tender layers of bulgogi beef. So burger is a sliiiiight misnomer, though the bun and toppings are definitely burgeresque. As someone who loves a good burger, it was a good presentation of a bulgogi sandwich. Bulgogi + melty white cheese (provolone?) beats out all but the very very best cheese steak for me.

I only worry that with such a large menu, not everything could be as good as what I had. I will definitely be back to find out!</review>

< Text>
Ample parking at various hours. Conveniently located next to the gold line metro and 101/110. It's also next to the serene LA public park - great for a warm-up before class. There are plenty of great offers, esp. for first timers. The staff is friendly and very knowledgeable, in contrast to generic gyms. Classes are informative and I always retain valuable info I could use later. Nice amenities (eg) towels, hygiene products in the shower...etc.

The main reason it doesn't get the full five starts is that some of the juicier classes don't fit my schedule. Also, membership is costly. The soap is very harsh on my hair.< /Text>

<date>1598988729165</date><rating>1</rating><username>T H<//username><gmap_id>0x80e82ebed5b30749:0x6a99858c7f6e0140< /gmap_id>< Text>
I had a simple leaking faucet like most people do so I called Dutton Plumbing in Santa Clarita. When the service tech arrived, I explained the problem and symptoms of the leak and showed him that when I applied light downward pressure to the hot water handle, the drip would stop. This guy, without ever looking under the sink or taking the water handle off to inspect the fixture told me that my entire faucet fixture would have to be rebuilt and replace the shut off valves under the sink or only replace the valves. Without inspecting the valves or the faucet itself, he gave a quote for $515 for replacing the valves and $795 for rebuilding the faucet and replacing the valves, both of which I declined as the cost seemed unusually high.

I emailed the company that manufactured the faucet and provided the exact same description of the problem via email that I gave Dutton Plumbing‚Äôs service tech in person. The faucet manufacturer replied back suggesting that I replace the seats and springs under the faucet handle and provided me with the part number. I purchased a two pack of the part for $4.98 and a tube of silicone grease for $4.00 at Home Depot and installed them myself in 10 minutes, resulting in the leak being fixed.

Dutton Plumbing not only misdiagnosed how to fix the leak, they suggested work that did not EVEN need to be done at the cost of nearly $800. They do this stuff for a living, so how could they not EVEN suggest replacing the seats and springs? But instead, he told me that I need to replace my entire faucet fixture and valve handles. I don't like being cheated and that is exactly what this place tried to do to me.

DO NOT let them do any work until you get a second opinion and estimate. They wanted to charge me $800 for work that did not need to be done AT ALL and I ended up fixing the leak myself and it literally cost me LESS THAN the price of a movie ticket. Read the Yelp reviews and you'll see a pattern of them trying to overcharge people.

I spoke to someone at the Dutton after they saw my review and he tried to make up an excuse, saying that they might suggest repairs that are "more comprehensive." There's a big difference between "more comprehensive" and repairs that are not required AT ALL. Crooks!<//Text>

Their rep showed up that day and immediately diagnosed the problem, quoted prices for several options and, when the replacement part was from an old outdated fixture, drove 20 miles to find it and came back the next morning to finish the job.  He was courteous, professional and extremely polite.  The price was very competitive.  I would add that the last time I had need of a plumber, I called the so-called "smell good" guys and I felt ripped off.  The $99 drain clog turned into a $1,000 replacement project.  I highly recommend Dutton Plumbing.< /Review>

< text>
Dutton staff are beyond professional - they are courteous and attentive, kind and polite. They treat you and your home with respect, using abundant covers to avoid tracking dirt and vacuums to minimize dust.  You get text  and images of the workers to ID who's coming to your house. <Resp>None</Resp><Name>Tyler Saunders</Name>< review>
I had a simple clog that couldn't be resolved with a bladder or consumer-grade auger. Heard good things about these guys from a friend, so I called. My call was answered by someone who spoke english, and was able to confirm a time to call me back to set an exact appointment time (same day). I didn't get a call back initially, so I called and rescheduled for the following day as I could not wait at home any longer. After that, smooth sailing. The dispatcher called me that next morning confirming a time, and then the repair man called me when he got there. He was cool enough to wait a few minutes for my fiance to get there. It took him 25 minutes to fix the clog and he was on his way. The price remained consistent, no surprises. This would have been 5 stars if I had initially gotten a call back like i was promised. However that being said, I would absolutely use these guys again.<//review>

I called Dutton because I had more then just a water plumbing issue with a newly purchased home. I had and issue with the gas line routing for the stove and a huge bird's nest of pipe and tubes for a reverse osmosis system under the kitchen sink that was leaking everywhere. He also broke several things in my bathroom and left glass all over the floor. He ripped the toilet up from the floor so now when anybody sits on it, it moves all over the place. He also left the toilet cover on my counter/in my sink. Since I gave him the benefit of the doubt, I believed him when he told me he fixed the problem and never mentioned about breaking anything. When my two year old and I walked into the bathroom we got glass in our feet. I called Dutton immediately and told them what happened and that they needed to send their employee back to fix what he broke. They could have cared less about the glass in my sons feet let alone mine. The rep was extremely rude and said he would call me back, never did. I called again and re-explained the situation and that rep was just as rude as the one before. Plumber never showed back up to fix what he broke, and no matter how many times I've called I've never gotten a call back. I opted for the slab fix..the by-pass option would also have fixed the hot water pipe leak in the slab. Within a 30 minutes Matt had located the exact location of the leak, and identified the hot water pipe. He prepared the work area, carefully removed 4 titles (without breaking them) and started the work to open up the cement to access the pipe.  Matt found the copper pipe with the leak. He then very carefully silver soldered the new pipe in place, wrapped the pipe with a thick rubber jacket, back-filled the hole in the slab, poured in quick drying cement to seal the floor. Matt‚Äôs work was meticulous, neat and professional. I am one happy customer ..and would recommend you call Dutton Plumbing if you ever need a professional plumbing job. Thanks again Matt for your expertise it is much appreciated.  Tony</review></record>

<review>I had a drainage leak beneath my kitchen sink.  I tried fixing it for three days myself but it would not stop leaking. Admitting defeat I called Dutton Plumbing.  They sent on over Steve S. who looked over the situation and gave me an estimate.  Normally I would have gotten three bids but after three days of fighting leaks that trashed my bottom cabinet shelf, I relented figuring if it was good enough for Mom, then go with it.  Steve explained the piping was the PVC pipe, gaskets and slip rings were old and best replaced entirely. After four hours of work, except for the Garbage Disposal, everything was replaced. The leaks stopped. Cost was not cheap but the fix seemed to be working and with a year warranty on their work, I was satisfied. Unfortunately the next day a weep formed under my right sink .  I called Dutton Plumbing and set up another appointment.  They wanted to send Steve out again to repair it but he was diverted for an emergency repair.  However they honored their warranty and sent out Juan P.  who determined another gasket was needed and fixed the issue at no further cost.  It is now three days later and no further leaks as of the writing of this review.  My wife and I say MOM Approves.< /review>< Pics>

After having called numerous local plumbers who didn't bother to show up or even call back, I called Dutton Plumbing to fix an outdoor PVC pipe leak, and I couldn't be happier. Dan & Jake were 100% professionals and fixed the problem in 40 minutes. Even the dispatcher on their customer service line was helpful.

Ritz Plumbing tried and failed to fix the pipes 5 times in a row and - in fact, made the problem worse after each visit. After Ritz Plumbing gave up (and tried to extort additional money for warranty work), Dutton Plumbing was there to pick up the pieces AND show me exactly what negligence and shoddy workmanship caused my the leak in the first place.

Dan & Jake were knowledgeable, experienced, and more than helpful with their explanations and suggestions. They showed up ON TIME and within hours of being called. They even stayed on for an extra hour or so after the job was completed so they could test that the leak was indeed corrected. Dutton Plumbing warrants the work for 1 year after the visit and as Dan put it: "We will own our mistakes and not charge you extra."  Too bad more companies aren't like this.</Review>

<user_name>Anna J< /user_name><Date>1522103761534< /Date><Rate>5< /Rate>< review>
Danny D and Leo B provided service for our residence on a leaking faucet and water pressure regulator. Danny was the main technician and Leo assisted him. Danny was very knowledgable, professional, courteous and friendly. He took time to explain the problem to us, how he planned to approach remedying it and the relative costs. As for expertise and professionalism, their service was excellent. I was especially pleased by Dan's positive professional demeanor. They were prompt, finished the work within the quoted timeframe, explained their process beforehand so we knew exactly what services we were receiving, and they left their workspace as clean as they found it. As for cost, we have worked with less expensive plumbers in the past, so Dutton is not the most competitive provider in terms of pricing, however with Dan's professionalism and a very organized business service model (we have not experienced a more organized effort, from front office to completion), customers can reasonably expect to pay a bit more than what a sole provider/owner-operator would charge that doesn't offer such a comprehensive service model, which includes your initial call, prompt scheduling, phone updates, e-mail updates and accurate time estimations for both technician arrival and work performance. We might have been able to shop around for a cheaper solution since this call was not an emergency call, but overall, we feel we have received value for our dollar.<//review>

<Text>My parent's just purchased a mobile home and the hot water heater was broken. They called Dutton Plumbing to come out and Diego was the technician at that time. My dad being a contractor was sure we would have to replace it. Diego could have easily taken their money and replaced the water heater with no complaints from them but instead, he took his time, looked everything over and found a fantastic solution to not have to replace the whole water heater. In the end, Diego saved my parents over a thousand dollars and was extremely friendly.

I called Dutton Plumbing because they all showed up at Starbucks in Porter Ranch on a number of occasions and bought everyone coffee.  They quickly schedule a plumber to come fix my broken shut off valve for the backyard irrigation so there would be no further flooding.  I received an email shortly thereafter with a picture of Jake M who would be coming to fix my broken valve.  When he arrived, he discovered that the shut off valve from the city was frozen shut, so he had to call DWP to come and close the valve.  They said it might be 2 - 3 hours or longer, and he told me just to call him whenever DWP showed up and he would come back and fix my broken valve.  He then called DWP to have them come turn the water back on, and, since he could not test the new valve he installed, Jake showed me how to check it.  He said if there was any leakage to call him and he would come right back and fix any problems.  I know the complication with the city's valve made extra work for him, but I was not charged any additional fee, and he got me a $50 discount coupon because I called after meeting Dutton Plumbing at Starbucks.  I could not be more satisfied for the professionalism that Jake demonstrated, and his willingness to see the job through no matter what extra time or inconvenience arose due to outside complications.  Without reservation, I extend my highest recommendation for Dutton Plumbing because of the outstanding service that Jake provided.< /Review>

<Text>We've been on the family service plan with Dutton Pluming of a few years now. To prevent these issues, Dutton Plumbing installed a pressure control regulator 3 or 4 years ago, but warned the hard water in the area would take its toll.  This year we had two more leaks.  We requested Luis Zamarripa as our annual service technician.  He is an excellent, dependable technician and he drives PINK DUTTON PLUMBING TRUCK.  10% of the profits from the PINK trucks go to the Susan G. Komen Foundation.
